MindWave 🌊 invests in building a strong community of dedicated experts with its consultants and clients. We also aim to be the movement of change that provides a better way of working and growing together.

We believe in a more human way of working. We just choose to do it differently! 🚀

Our client portfolio consists of large companies in FinTech, Pharma, Media and many more.




About the role

MindWave is looking for Big Data Software Engineers to join our talented team of engineers!

The position is for a brand new initiative to overhaul the data management processes in an established enterprise in the FinTech industry.




What you'll be doing

As a senior data engineer/developer, you will be part of a dynamic team where you will be working on data flows interacting with various systems using various protocols. As we are building a data management platform as part of the strategy to enable frictionless transaction, you together with our dynamic team of professionals using up-to-date technologies will be delivering data management features and capabilities managing & delivering data across different business practices internally and externally. You will develop the platform that is based on industry best practices, standards and governance framework that are robust, scalable & performant as well as ensuring high data quality and data integrity.




Qualifications

Professional skills

At least 8+ years’ experience in Software development/data engineer practices/consulting;
University bachelor’s or master’s degree in computer science or related engineering discipline;
Strong communication skills (both written and verbal);
Team player, willing to work in a multicultural environment;
Able to lead, coach and groom junior team members.

Technical skills

Proven experience in data engineering and software development practices;
Solid programming/coding experience in Java Development;
Solid understanding of data engineering & ETL Development ;
Having experience in data API and solid understanding of distributed system is a strong advantage;
Having experience with SQL, PL/SQL in Oracle DB;
Hands-on experience on Denodo, Cloudera or any data management platform is a strong advantage;
Hands-on experience with Apache NiFi, Kafka, Spark, Hadoop is a strong advantage;
Hands-on experience with AWS managed services such as Amazon Kinesis, MSK, Redshift, S3 is a plus;
Experience with CICD development & deployment tools such as Maven, Jenkins, Nexus and Git;
Experience with scripting language, primarily Unix Shell, Perl, Python;
Having expertise in manual & automation testing;
Practical working experience in an Agile development (scrum) context;
Proven experience as a key technical resource leading the development of solutions;
Demonstrated ability to influence and consult (providing options with pros, cons and risks) around all key technical decisions during project delivery;
Knows or wants to learn how to translate business problems into software & technical requirements;
Strong interpersonal skills, customer centric attitude, ability to deal with cultural diversity;
Proven team player and team builder;
Demonstrated aptitude for learning new technologies quickly;
Able to thrive in a fast paced, goals and deadlines driven environment;
Passionate about change & improvement and constantly challenging the status quo.




What we offer

Attractive salary package;
Compensation package that includes private medical and life insurance, meal vouchers, mobile and internet plan;
Homeworking as default!
Be part of an awesome group of people 😎




Equal Opportunities

MindWave is an equal opportunity employer. All aspects of employment, including hiring, promotion, remuneration, or discipline, are based solely on performance, competence, conduct, or business needs.

It takes powerful technology to connect our brands and partners with an audience of nearly 900 million. Whether you’re looking to write mobile app code, engineer the servers behind our massive ad tech stacks, or develop algorithms to help us process trillions of data points a day, what you do here will have a huge impact on our business—and the world. Want in?




A Little Bit About Us - The Data and Common Services (DCS) team within the Yahoo Advertising Engineering organization is responsible for the Advertising core data infrastructure and services that provide common, horizontal services for user and contextual targeting, privacy and analytics. We are looking for a talented ML engineer to join the modeling and scoring team. As a member of the team, you will be helping our Ad platforms to deliver highly accurate and relevant Advertising experiences for our consumers and for the web at large scale using AI technologies.




Responsibilities




Work with data scientists and product teams to understand and address end to end requirements for the purpose of prototype development as well as production software development;
Build large scale distributed machine learning architecture on public and private clouds;
Perform large scale machine learning operations including feature engineering, model tuning, model deployment and performance monitoring.
Utilizes experience with distributed file systems, database architecture, and data modeling to organize and process large data sets;
Build streaming platform by leveraging latest streaming technologies to support research and production needs;
Identify potential performance bottlenecks and scalability issues to justify or critique the design of new algorithms;
Work with modern development methodology such as Agile, Scrum, Test Driven Development and SDLC




Minimum Qualifications




M.S. Computer Science or Engineering or B.S. of related fields;
Ability to work in a fast paced, intellectually challenging and highly technical environment;
Strong programming skills in Java/Python/Spark Scala/SQL;
Good knowledge and experience with big data technologies including Hadoop/Hive/Spark/Flink is highly desirable;
Good knowledge of machine learning including feature engineering, decision trees, MLPs, logistic regression, transformer (BERT/GPT) is highly desirable;
Experience with building robust, scalable, distributed services;
Experience with massively scalable messaging and distributed real-time processing;
Experience with AWS and AWS SageMaker is highly desirable;
Experience in all aspects of software development including architecture and design, implementation and production support;
Knowledge of CI/CD and DevOps tools and processes;
Excellent written and verbal communication skills




Yahoo is proud to be an equal opportunity workplace. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to, and will not be discriminated against based on age, race, gender, color, religion, national origin, sexual orientation, gender identity, veteran status, disability or any other protected category. Yahoo is dedicated to providing an accessible environment for all candidates during the application process and for employees during their employment. If you need accessibility assistance and/or a reasonable accommodation due to a disability, please submit a request via the Accommodation Request Form (www.yahooinc.com/careers/contact-us.html) or call 408-336-1409. Requests and calls received for non-disability related issues, such as following up on an application, will not receive a response.




Yahoo has a high degree of flexibility around employee location and hybrid working. In fact, our flexible-hybrid approach to work is one of the things our employees rave about. Most roles don’t require specific regular patterns of in-person office attendance. If you join Yahoo, you may be asked to attend (or travel to attend) on-site work sessions, team-building, or other in-person events. When these occur, you’ll be given notice to make arrangements.




If you’re curious about how this factors into this role, please discuss with the recruiter.




Currently work for Yahoo? Please apply on our internal career site.

